snippet.title: Graceland Above - Barron Trump Sings About ELVIS!
snippet.description:
Graceland Above

Check us out on Spotify! https://open.spotify.com/album/3y1CZVxPBVqYl2ljdNVWno?si=lLRWLYbeQcuXD9TQDeKi7A

⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0

Lyrics:
"Graceland Above"
By Barron Trump (in the style of Elvis)

Verse 1
Woke up this mornin’ with a fire in my soul
Didn’t need no headlines, didn’t check no polls
I grabbed my coat, combed back my hair
And I whispered, “Thank You, Lord,” with a voice full of air

Chorus
I’m singin’ hallelujah in blue suede shoes
A king may fall, but He don’t lose
From the White House walls to the chapel dove
Ain’t no mansion like Graceland above

Verse 2
I’ve seen the power, I’ve seen the fame
But none of that glory matches His name
Not in the gold or the Mar-a-Lago breeze
Only in the quiet when I fall to my knees

Chorus
I’m singin’ hallelujah in blue suede shoes
A king may fall, but He don’t lose
From the White House walls to the chapel dove
Ain’t no mansion like Graceland above

Bridge
I don’t need a crowd or a spotlight beam
Just a backbeat prayer and a holy dream
With a voice like velvet, and a heart set free
I’m swingin’ for heaven in key of E

Final Chorus
I’m singin’ hallelujah, hips might swing
But the praise I bring, now that’s the real King
He lifts me higher than the eagles shove
Ain’t no throne like Graceland above

Outro
So I’ll croon these hymns ‘til I’m called back home
Not alone—no, never alone
‘Cause I got the Lord and a gospel groove
And this Presley praise is how I move
